job_description:
We are currently looking for a skilled Senior Business Analyst to join our team. Our Senior Business Analyst works to evaluate the business needs of our valued clients and create solutions to fuel their success. As a Senior Business Analyst on our team, you will have the opportunity to apply innovation practices to help improve ours and our customers’ purchasing and product experiences.




 OUR PERFECT CANDIDATE 





 7 years of relevant business experience; 
 Bachelor’s degree preferred; 
 Strong business analysis skills (planning, feasibility assessments, requirements development, testing, problem solving, working across business and IT); 
 Excellent attention to detail and results oriented with a track record demonstrating strong problem solving and analytical skills; 
 Ability to quickly learn complex business processes and understand the underlying transactional systems; 
 Strong oral, written and presentation skills; ability to communicate across all levels; 
 Experience in data and process automation; Salesforce administration and design a plus. 







 KEY QUALIFICATIONS / RESPONSIBILITIES 





 Get, analyze, decompose, and fix project requirements; 
 Maintain project documentation (user stories, acceptance criteria, etc.); 
 Synchronize the visions of the project by all participants (both internal and external); 
 Analyze the competitors; 
 Analyze the project market; 
 Work on improvements to current projects and preseale; 
 Generate ideas that will increase the business value of the product; 
 Communicate with the client and the team; 
 Work with client expectations; 
 Encourage upsales on current projects; 
 Validate and process a presale and participate in closing the deal. 







 EMPLOYMENT CONDITIONS FOR THIS ROLE 




 A friendly team of professionals: 

 Strong technical specialists who are ready to help solve problems. 

 Professional development: 

 Financial and 1-to-1 meetings to discuss development plans; 
 Individual Development Plan; 
 Paid conferences and certifications; 
 Lectures and other events where senior specialists share their knowledge with junior and middle specialists; 
 Knowledge Bases with useful information for development. 

 Vertical development: 

 Opportunity to grow and become a coordinator and further a Technology Lead. 

 Work-life advantages: 

 Flexible working hours; 
 24 calendar days of vacation per year and paid sick leaves; 
 Financial support and gifts for important events.
